The paper deals with the problem of providing understandable and useful explanations for black-box machine learning models, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of these explanations in high-risk domains such as health-care or defense, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential consequences of failure in these domains, which could relate to the field of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or cryptography (cs.CR).
